    "created_at": "2011-07-11T20:00:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2011-07-11T20:00:10Z",
    "body": "The variable binding isn't really the same block, though. The following example does the same thing:\n\n<pre>\nfn main() {\n    let int a = 5;\n    {\n        let int b = a;\n        let str a = \"something\";\n        ret b;\n    }\n}\n</pre>\n\n\nDo we want to disallow shadowing in nested blocks?\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
