    "created_at": "2011-07-12T06:01:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2011-07-12T06:01:13Z",
    "body": "Yes, shadowing in nested blocks should shadow normally. The issue with the first snippet is that, in our current scoping model, there is no way to get at the parameter named a, since it will be shadowed through the whole body. Thus, I think we should treat the body scope and the parameter scope as a single scope (and similarly for loop bodies + loop vars, case bodies + bindings).\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
